public final void dispose()
Description copied from interface: IAPIClient
Disposes this client instance. This method releases any required resources. After this method returns the client is no longer in a usable state. This method must be implemented in a thread-safe way.

sendRequest

protected final de.codesourcery.eve.apiclient.InternalAPIResponse sendRequest(ICredentialsProvider credentialsProvider,
                                                                              IResponseParser parser,
                                                                              java.lang.String relativePath,
                                                                              java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> requestParams,
                                                                              APIKey.KeyRole requiredKeyRole,
                                                                              IErrorHandler errorHandler,
                                                                              boolean force)
                                                                       throws java.io.IOException
Send request.

Parameters:
credentialsProvider - credentials provider, may be null if this method is invoked with a key role of APIKey.KeyRole.NONE_REQUIRED
parser - parser that should be used to parse the response
relativePath - request path, relative to setBaseURI(URI)
requestParams - the request paramters WITHOUT apiKey / userID (will be automatically added if required)
requiredKeyRole - role of the key required for the request, APIKey.KeyRole.NONE_REQUIRED if the request does not require authentication
errorHandler - Error handler to use, null to use the default handler
force - set to true to force retrieval of a fresh result, otherwise a cached response might be returned. Note that forcing a request will do nothing if the server's last response included a cachedUntil field and the indicated time has not been elapsed yet.
Returns:
Throws:
java.io.IOException
